# LLM Answer Watcher - Environment Variables Example
#
# This file shows the environment variables needed to run LLM Answer Watcher.
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual API keys.
#
# IMPORTANT: Never commit .env files with real API keys to version control!

# ============================================================================
# OpenAI API Key
# ============================================================================
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Required if you're using OpenAI models (gpt-4o-mini, gpt-4o, etc.)
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# ============================================================================
# Anthropic API Key
# ============================================================================
# Get your API key from: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
# Required if you're using Anthropic models (Claude 3.5 Haiku, Sonnet, etc.)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_api_key_here

# ============================================================================
# Mistral API Key
# ============================================================================
# Get your API key from: https://console.mistral.ai/api-keys/
# Required if you're using Mistral models
MISTRAL_API_KEY=your_mistral_api_key_here

# ============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy this file to .env in the project root:
#    cp examples/.env.example .env
#
# 2. Edit .env and replace the placeholder values with your actual API keys
#
# 3. Make sure .env is in .gitignore (it should be by default)
#
# 4. Load environment variables before running:
#    - If using the CLI directly, variables are loaded automatically
#    - If using python-dotenv: python-dotenv run llm-answer-watcher run --config ...
#    - Or export them manually: export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
#
# 5. Verify your config with:
#    llm-answer-watcher validate --config examples/watcher.config.yaml
#
# ============================================================================
# Security Best Practices
# ============================================================================
#
# ✅ DO:
# - Keep API keys in environment variables (never hardcode)
# - Use .env files locally (never commit to git)
# - Rotate API keys regularly
# - Use separate keys for development and production
# - Set spending limits on API provider dashboards
#
# ❌ DON'T:
# - Commit .env files to version control
# - Share API keys in chat, email, or screenshots
# - Use production keys in development
# - Store keys in code or config files
# - Reuse keys across multiple applications
#
# ============================================================================
# Cost Management
# ============================================================================
#
# The tool estimates costs before running:
# - gpt-4o-mini: ~$0.0001-0.0005 per query
# - gpt-4o: ~$0.005-0.02 per query
# - claude-3-5-haiku: ~$0.001-0.005 per query
# - claude-3-5-sonnet: ~$0.005-0.03 per query
#
# Set API rate limits on provider dashboards to prevent accidental overuse.
# Use the --yes flag carefully in automation to avoid unexpected costs.
#
# ============================================================================
